	<xsd:complexType name="JournalEntryType" id="oagis-id-2f30429934904701b1a6406d005dd6c2">
		<xsd:annotation>
			<xsd:documentation source="http://www.openapplications.org/oagis/10">A journal represents a change in the balances of a business's financial accounts.  Many tasks or transactions throughout an enterprise will result in the creation of a journal.  Some examples are creating a customer invoice, paying a vendor, transferring inventory, or paying employees.  A journal consists of a header with general information, and two or more lines specifying what accounts will be affected.  A journal typically includes balanced debit and credit lines.</xsd:documentation>
		</xsd:annotation>
